Module 26 – Vexatious ≠ Frivolous 📚🚫

Core Message

Being called vexatious doesn’t mean your filings lack merit — and the label can be fought.

⸻

Lesson Introduction

Courts may try to deter repeat filings by labeling you “vexatious.” This can be challenged if you can show each filing was necessary.

⸻

Teaching Block

1. Demand Specificity
	•	Ask the court to identify which filings were frivolous.

2. Show Legitimate Purpose
	•	Document the procedural necessity of each filing.

3. Counter with Pattern
	•	Show that the court accepts similar volume from represented parties.

⸻

Real-World Illustration

An Arizona filing combined a procedural necessity log with legal precedent to overturn a vexatious designation.

⸻

Assignment Prompt

Task:
Draft a two-sentence rebuttal to a vexatious claim.

⸻

Model Answer (Sample)

“Each filing advanced the litigation by adding unrebutted facts or new legal authority. None were repetitive or filed to harass.”

⸻

Reflection Summary

Vexatious ≠ without merit.

⸻

Visual Pairing

Image Concept:
A dictionary showing “vexatious” crossed out, replaced with “necessary.” Caption:
“Purpose Protects You.”
